commit.message:
Update make_doc

Add 'set -e' so that errors abort the script (otherwise it is very
easy to miss if some step of the process fails).

Also switch to using pdftex to produce a .pdf version of the manual.

Make HTML version of docs more readable

... by removing the custom alias \x for \times, and replacing \pif by ' -- in
both cases this helps tth (a tool used by convert.pl to produce the HTML
version of the manual) which does not know how to deal with \x and \pif.
http -> https
CI: tweak concurrency limiting

commit.message:
Refine filters for a NormalizerInGLnZ method

This fixes a warning that show up if one starts the upcoming GAP 4.11 with the `-N`
command line option, and then loads this package.

For some information on the background of this, see also
<https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/1649> and
<https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/2336>
